{
  "texts": [
    "(Oroojlooy & Hajinezhad, 2021) Team homogeneity allows for parameter sharing among agents and simpler network architectures, which leads to faster and more stable training.",
    "However, a multi-agent team will likely have a heterogeneous composition.",
    "Agents must leverage their unique abilities and rely on other agents' specializations to cooperate and find effective policies.",
    "Another distinction between RL agents is regarding the synchronicity of the decisions and updates of agents.",
    "A system is considered synchronous if there is a global clock and agents move in lockstep."
  ]
}